<TITLE> Manzur pledges to spend public money honestly </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, May 29 (bdnews24.com)BNP backed Chittagong mayoral candidate, M Manzur Alam, pledged to spend the public money with honesty and improve civic facilities if elected. He made the pledge during the day-long campaign on Saturday, organised by BNP and its associate organisations. Officially a candidate of a civic movement in Chittagong, Manzur Alam, exchanged views with leaders of the BNP and its associate organisations of different wards at his house at North Kattolli at around 10am. Following the meeting he sat with labour organisations of Halishahar and Bandar. He participated in a meeting at Railway Public School of the city organised by Bangladesh Teachers Association at noon. Chittagong city BNP vice-president Dastagir Chowdhury, Shamsul Alam and local BNP leaders accompanied Manzur on his campaign trail. bdnews24
